  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "in `PendingTransactions.java` we have inconsistant use of synchronization blocks.  Sometimes we get a lock on `pendingTransactions`, sometimes we don't.  What's curious is that `pendingTransactions` is itself a `ConcurrentHashMap` so it should be thread safe.  And the internals of the concurrent map also locks on itself, potentially causing dead locks.\r\n\r\nWe should revisit the code and make sure we need the sync blocks and if so we need to ensure they don't deadlock.  Similarly to `prioritizedTransactions`.  If we need a lock we should have a lock that is not the hash map.  We should also document why we need the syncs if they stay.  \r\n\r\nBut the first course of action should be to examine if the sync blocks can simply be removed.",
